Clinical Reasoning:
Stopko tips are typically used during root canal treatments where thorough irrigation and drying of the pulp chamber is essential. Among the given options, only option A contains Sodium Hypochlorite (NaOCl) along with chelator EDTA, making it suitable for effective pulpal disinfection and preparation before obturation.
Answer: \boxed{A} Based on the clinical need for thorough irrigation and drying of the pulp chamber using Stopko tips, Option A (5.25% NaOCl + 17% EDTA) provides the necessary chemical action for pulpal disinfection combined with a chelating effect to enhance efficacy. Other options do not offer the required combination for optimal root canal preparation. Answer: \boxed{A}
